Colombia Stocks: Coltejer, Fabricato Decline; Interbolsa Rises

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-04-15T15:45:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/colombia-stocks-coltejer-fabricato-decline-interbolsa-rises.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:07 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.1 percent to 14,078.10, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.2 percent to 1,666.30.  Textiles fell as  Colombia ’s peso rose 0.2 percent to 1,801
per  U.S. dollar , from 1,804.50 yesterday. The currency has
gained 0.9 percent this week, reducing revenue for exporters,
said Felipe Sanchez, analyst at brokerage Serfinco SA.  Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , the Medellin-based clothing maker
and exporter, dropped 1.2 percent to 86 centavos.  Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)  , Colombia’s
biggest textile maker, fell 0.2 percent to 43.9 pesos.  Pacific Rubiales (PREC CB), the most weighted stock on
Colombia’s exchange, rose 1.1 percent to 52,860 pesos. The
Toronto-based  oil company  with fields in Colombia gained on
oil’s rebound, as U.S. consumer sentiment improved and
industrial output increased.  Interbolsa SA (INTBOL SA), which holds the greatest market
share among Colombian brokerages, rose 0.5 percent to 2,785
pesos. The Medellin-based broker is involved in managing a
series of share issues including this week’s issues by Grupo
Aval and Avianca Taca Holding SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
